{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bb43c3bf-3c39-46ed-bf2a-90586e088070","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NPdZ9WroPBCvHhCAiyUNg5","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# compilation order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_012UuAwu5QCkqCw7Rtmt44Xn","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-3a5212987176431cad33c0b2dad65b84/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-3a5212987176431cad33c0b2dad65b84/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"e584bffb-4e4e-4b61-85ff-385552d34372","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — references `BrokenOrder.Domain` (from `Domain.fs`)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n3. `Program.fs` — references both\n\n`Services.fs` is compiled before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. The fix is to put `Domain.fs` first.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"C782:2E6B36:FA451C:139111E:69FFD736"},"id":"2c7984d5-afa8-490c-8b3c-2f8273565686","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:23.138Z","parentId":"b9d63863-f440-4f6b-bf26-f1d7cf73bc34"}
